    "created_at": "2014-02-24T22:32:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-02-24T22:32:16Z",
    "body": "I don't really think this is necessary. There's the `uninit` function for declaring an uninitialized variable. The ability to create raw pointers without `unsafe` is more of a novelty than something useful (real pointer arithmetic via `offset` is `unsafe` anyway).\n",
