    "created_at": "2014-02-25T04:31:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-02-25T04:31:17Z",
    "body": "It would still be nice to have this possible without an unsafe block, but it didn't come to mind that uninit() would work as a trapdoor here. Oversafety is less of a problem than inability to express immutable circular references.\n\nIt would be nice if we explicitly stated in docs that the reason to use uninit is to convince the compiler that a variable has been initialized without actually doing the work to initialize it (which is, of course, unsafe in general, unlike the suggested feature).\n",
